MR. KELLY: Objection. Argumentative, Your Honor.

THE COURT: Irrelevant. He's --

MR. KELLY: Irrelevant also.

(Laughter)

Q. (BY MR. BAKER) So Mr. Simpson gave you permission to take his blood
on June 13, after you had been with him for 30 minutes, correct?

MR. KELLY: Objection to the second half of that question, Your Honor.
