THE COURT: Overruled. Let's get on with it.

THE WITNESS: Yes.

Q. (BY MR. BAKER) And when you went down to take Mr. Simpson's blood,
did he have any attorneys with him?

A. No.

Q. And so it was just you, Mr. Lange, and Nurse Peratis, correct?

A. And Mr. Simpson, yes.

Q. Well, if you were going to take his blood, he ought to be there,
don't you think?

So at that time you had a photographer come in, did you not, to the
area where the nurse was taking Mr. Simpson's blood?

MR. KELLY: Objection. Beyond the scope, Your Honor.

THE COURT: Photographer came in. Overruled.

THE WITNESS: No. I didn't have a photographer come in there.

Q. (BY MR. BAKER) Well, a photographer came in and took a picture of
