When a stab wound is made, the opening is much larger, often, than the
knife -- of the blade itself, because as the stabbing occurs, the
victim moves away, the hand of the assailant follows, and there is
cutting, as well as stabbing.

Q. (BY MR. MEDVENE) The doctor was speaking about Exhibit 2004.

