or disagree?

MR. MEDVENE: Objection, your honor. Improper hypothetical.

THE COURT: Overruled.

MR. MEDVENE: Also compound.

THE WITNESS: This scenario that you have indicated is a different
case. That is totally impossible in so many places. I'd have to go
through them and tell you.

Q. Thank you.

Now, doctor, one area -- and I'm going to put up this hand. You talked
about abrasions and this hand being consistent with --

MR. P. BAKER: 878.

(Exhibit 878 displayed.)

