A. Well, there's no way to know precisely how that happened. Again, as
the glove on the hand possible primary. You can't rule out secondary.

Q. When you say "possible primary," what is possible?

MR. LEONARD: Calls for speculation, based on his last answer.

THE COURT: Overruled.

THE WITNESS: It could have been directly from contact, from contact
with the glove with the head, or it could have been contact the glove
with the shirt. That had cut hairs on it, as well. That would be a
secondary transfer, a close secondary.

Q. And the glove being deposited at Rockingham?

A. Right.

Q. Can you, if you wouldn't mind, on Nicole Brown to maybe under the
